  <name>FFwd UI</name>
  <summary>A minimalistic FFmpeg GUI for common video operations</summary>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      FFwd UI is a user-friendly desktop application for common FFmpeg operations built with Go, Wails, and Svelte.
      It provides a simple interface for video and audio manipulation tasks without requiring command-line knowledge.
    </p>
    <p>Features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Trim video from start or to specific length</li>
      <li>Trim video to a specific time range</li>
      <li>Extract audio tracks in various formats (MP3, AAC, WAV, FLAC)</li>
      <li>Convert between video formats</li>
      <li>Change video resolution with hardware acceleration support</li>
      <li>Adjust audio volume</li>
      <li>Crop video to specific dimensions</li>
      <li>Adjust video and audio bitrates</li>
      <li>Add padding (silence/blank video) to beginning and end</li>
      <li>Real-time progress tracking</li>
      <li>Command preview before execution</li>
      <li>Disk space monitoring</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  
